WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.970
- Today I learned that Emily Bader

00:00:02.970 --> 00:00:05.101
doesn't like a creepy whisper.

00:00:05.101 --> 00:00:06.030
[Tom whispering]

00:00:06.030 --> 00:00:06.863
- Do it again.

00:00:06.863 --> 00:00:07.696
[Tom whispering]

00:00:07.696 --> 00:00:08.760
No, it's not growing on me.

00:00:08.760 --> 00:00:09.593
- Hi, "Vogue."

00:00:09.593 --> 00:00:10.557
I'm Tom Blyth.

00:00:10.557 --> 00:00:13.804
- And I'm Emily Bader, and
this is "Off the Cuff."

00:00:13.804 --> 00:00:15.484
[light music]
- Round one, icebreakers.

00:00:15.484 --> 00:00:16.317
[Emily shuddering]

00:00:16.317 --> 00:00:18.780
One memory you'd love to relive on repeat.

00:00:18.780 --> 00:00:20.580
- When I went sailing for the first time

00:00:20.580 --> 00:00:22.050
and I was super hungover in Sweden,

00:00:22.050 --> 00:00:23.850
and it was actually the
greatest memory of my life.

00:00:23.850 --> 00:00:24.683
- That's so beautiful.

00:00:24.683 --> 00:00:26.550
- If we got kicked out of somewhere,

00:00:26.550 --> 00:00:28.620
what would the reason be?

00:00:28.620 --> 00:00:29.760
- Drunk and disorderly.

00:00:29.760 --> 00:00:31.470
- No, we're so well-behaved.

00:00:31.470 --> 00:00:32.303
Never.
[cards thudding]

00:00:32.303 --> 00:00:33.870
- What useless skill are you proud of?

00:00:33.870 --> 00:00:36.240
- I can hold my breath for a
really long time underwater,

00:00:36.240 --> 00:00:38.220
but I can't pop my ears very well,

00:00:38.220 --> 00:00:39.053
so there's not really a point

00:00:39.053 --> 00:00:40.037
to being able to do that.
- That's not useless.

00:00:40.037 --> 00:00:40.870
That's very helpful.

00:00:40.870 --> 00:00:44.439
- If you had to replace
a finger with a tool,

00:00:44.439 --> 00:00:46.413
[chuckling] what would it be?

00:00:48.900 --> 00:00:51.270
- Swiss Army Knife, so you've
got multiple tools in one.

00:00:51.270 --> 00:00:52.103
- [Emily] That's genius.

00:00:52.103 --> 00:00:52.936
- Yep.

00:00:52.936 --> 00:00:54.300
What word do you struggle to pronounce?

00:00:54.300 --> 00:00:55.470
- I'm gonna do it right out.

00:00:55.470 --> 00:00:57.550
Horseradish.

00:00:57.550 --> 00:00:59.267
I always say horshradish.

00:00:59.267 --> 00:01:00.100
- Horshradish.

00:01:00.100 --> 00:01:01.183
- But it's just horseradish.

00:01:01.183 --> 00:01:02.161
- Nice.

00:01:02.161 --> 00:01:03.333
- Right, how do you, is that right?

00:01:03.333 --> 00:01:04.620
- Horseradish.
- Horseradish.

00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:07.050
What's one thing that you
pretend to understand?

00:01:07.050 --> 00:01:07.883
- Math.

00:01:07.883 --> 00:01:08.716
- [Emily] [laughing] Yeah?

00:01:08.716 --> 00:01:09.810
- I don't even pretend.

00:01:09.810 --> 00:01:13.142
If I were a sound effect,
what would it sound like?

00:01:13.142 --> 00:01:14.275
- Skibbidy bop.

00:01:14.275 --> 00:01:15.108
- [Emily And Tom] Skibiddy bo, oh, oh.

00:01:15.954 --> 00:01:16.999
[light music]
- [Emily] Round two.

00:01:16.999 --> 00:01:17.832
- [Emily And Tom] Film.

00:01:17.832 --> 00:01:18.990
- Go.
- Okay, okay, okay.

00:01:18.990 --> 00:01:21.840
When you first met me, what
movie trope did I embody?

00:01:21.840 --> 00:01:24.021
An example, main
character, funny sidekick,

00:01:24.021 --> 00:01:25.429
mysterious stranger.
- Mysterious stranger

00:01:25.429 --> 00:01:27.673
with the leather jackets
and the motorcycle.

00:01:27.673 --> 00:01:28.506
I mean,

00:01:28.506 --> 00:01:29.339
what's more mysterious?
- Did you know

00:01:29.339 --> 00:01:30.630
that was one of them already?

00:01:30.630 --> 00:01:31.463
- Yep.
- That was so good.

00:01:31.463 --> 00:01:32.520
- [chuckling] No, I just knew.
[card thudding]

00:01:32.520 --> 00:01:36.360
If we ran into each other in
a grocery aisle rom-com style,

00:01:36.360 --> 00:01:38.040
what are we each holding?

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:39.255
This is actually very telling.

00:01:39.255 --> 00:01:40.588
- A cucumber.

00:01:40.588 --> 00:01:41.421
- A cucumber?

00:01:41.421 --> 00:01:42.930
Okay, perfect.
[Tom and Emily laughing]

00:01:42.930 --> 00:01:44.990
- Is there one specific movie scene

00:01:44.990 --> 00:01:47.077
that is on repeat in your head?

00:01:47.077 --> 00:01:49.230
- "Sexy cardi," which I
don't know what that's from.

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:50.193
- [Tom] What is that?

00:01:50.193 --> 00:01:53.557
- And also when Cher slaps
Nicolas Cage in "Moonstruck."

00:01:53.557 --> 00:01:54.391
- "Moonstruck."
- And says, "Snap out of it."

00:01:54.391 --> 00:01:55.224
- You were just talking about that.

00:01:55.224 --> 00:01:56.057
You love that.
- Yeah.

00:01:56.057 --> 00:01:56.890
- Okay.
[card thudding]

00:01:56.890 --> 00:01:58.290
- If I disappeared for 10 minutes on set,

00:01:58.290 --> 00:02:00.000
where would you first
look for me? [chuckling]

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:01.260
- Crafty.
- Crafty.

00:02:01.260 --> 00:02:02.093
Snacks.

00:02:02.093 --> 00:02:03.420
- What kind of person are you

00:02:03.420 --> 00:02:05.250
on the last night of your vacation?

00:02:05.250 --> 00:02:07.440
- Oh, I'm in bed early
and I'm watching HGTV,

00:02:07.440 --> 00:02:09.440
locked in, bathrobe, take, yep, that.

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:10.830
- On the last night of your vacation?

00:02:10.830 --> 00:02:12.480
- I like to be rested for the morning.

00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:13.380
I've done all the fun things.

00:02:13.380 --> 00:02:14.280
- All you're doing is leaving.

00:02:14.280 --> 00:02:15.240
You might as well go all out.

00:02:15.240 --> 00:02:16.073
- That's my answer, Tom.

00:02:16.073 --> 00:02:17.026
- Okay, fine, fair enough.
[Emily chuckling]

00:02:17.026 --> 00:02:17.859
Who am I to argue?

00:02:17.859 --> 00:02:19.920
- If your acting career
had chapter titles,

00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:21.903
which chapter are you in right now?

00:02:21.903 --> 00:02:23.567
- Eh, I'm enjoying it.

00:02:23.567 --> 00:02:25.560
I'm just lapping it all up.

00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:26.657
- He's in the lapping it all up chapter.

00:02:26.657 --> 00:02:28.390
- I'm in the lapping stage, yeah.

00:02:28.390 --> 00:02:30.599
[light music]
Round three, fashion.

00:02:30.599 --> 00:02:31.432
- [Emily] Fashion.

00:02:31.432 --> 00:02:33.960
- What's your most
unforgettable corset moment?

00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:36.390
- Riding a horse with the
double corset down Dover Castle.

00:02:36.390 --> 00:02:38.040
If you had to save one piece of clothing

00:02:38.040 --> 00:02:41.640
from a moth infestation,
what would you choose?

00:02:41.640 --> 00:02:42.660
- These boots.

00:02:42.660 --> 00:02:44.670
What's your beauty mantra?

00:02:44.670 --> 00:02:46.616
- Nothing looks better
than good night of sleep.

00:02:46.616 --> 00:02:48.210
[chuckling] What's the
best fashion compliment

00:02:48.210 --> 00:02:49.684
you've ever received?

00:02:49.684 --> 00:02:51.157
- Mm, I don't know.

00:02:51.157 --> 00:02:52.980
- "You look real English."

00:02:52.980 --> 00:02:53.813
- No.

00:02:53.813 --> 00:02:55.050
"You look good, kid"

00:02:55.050 --> 00:02:56.329
I don't know.
- "You look good, kid"

00:02:56.329 --> 00:02:57.570
[Tom and Emily laughing]

00:02:57.570 --> 00:02:59.370
- What's your go-to airport look?

00:02:59.370 --> 00:03:02.250
- The worst outfit I own
in my closet and Uggs.

00:03:02.250 --> 00:03:04.950
Did an outfit ever give
you a new personality?

00:03:04.950 --> 00:03:06.900
- Yes, actually.

00:03:06.900 --> 00:03:09.690
The moment I started
wearing boots with heels,

00:03:09.690 --> 00:03:12.370
with a decent heel,
suddenly, I've just, like,

00:03:12.370 --> 00:03:13.499
I was 10 times more confident.

00:03:13.499 --> 00:03:15.460
- Yeah, that's such, like,
a look, with the earring.

00:03:15.460 --> 00:03:16.440
[light music]
- Round four,

00:03:16.440 --> 00:03:18.180
the last time you,

00:03:18.180 --> 00:03:19.020
dot, dot, dot.
- Oh.

00:03:19.020 --> 00:03:20.610
Got humbled instantly.

00:03:20.610 --> 00:03:21.443
Ooh.

00:03:21.443 --> 00:03:22.644
- You humble me every time we hang out.

00:03:22.644 --> 00:03:23.696
- [chuckling] Tom, no.

00:03:23.696 --> 00:03:24.529
- [Tom] Yep.

00:03:24.529 --> 00:03:25.587
- It's an honor to do that.
- Yeah, thank you.

00:03:25.587 --> 00:03:28.170
Had a paranormal encounter?

00:03:28.170 --> 00:03:29.970
- Ooh, a Christmas a few years ago,

00:03:29.970 --> 00:03:32.906
I felt some crazy grandma presence.

00:03:32.906 --> 00:03:33.739
- [Tom] Oh.
- Yeah.

00:03:33.739 --> 00:03:34.730
- Your grandma or somebody else's grandma?

00:03:34.730 --> 00:03:35.563
- My grandma.

00:03:35.563 --> 00:03:36.900
The lights, there was red.

00:03:36.900 --> 00:03:38.220
- [Tom] Oh.
- I'll get into it later.

00:03:38.220 --> 00:03:39.053
- [Tom] That's nice.

00:03:39.053 --> 00:03:40.680
- Edited your Wikipedia page? [chuckling]

00:03:40.680 --> 00:03:41.580
- Never.

00:03:41.580 --> 00:03:43.680
- Yeah, how do you even
do that, is that a thing?

00:03:43.680 --> 00:03:44.704
- Doesn't somebody else do that?

00:03:44.704 --> 00:03:46.350
- I thought it was a job, but. [chuckling]

00:03:46.350 --> 00:03:48.270
- Had beef with an inanimate object?

00:03:48.270 --> 00:03:50.670
- The tray on the last airplane
that I couldn't figure out

00:03:50.670 --> 00:03:51.630
how to get outta the tray.

00:03:51.630 --> 00:03:52.710
Went camping?

00:03:52.710 --> 00:03:53.877
- Last summer, I think, at some point.

00:03:53.877 --> 00:03:55.320
Yeah, I did, I did.

00:03:55.320 --> 00:03:56.790
I went this summer.

00:03:56.790 --> 00:03:58.245
- What an adventurous guy.
- In Canada.

00:03:58.245 --> 00:03:59.078
In Canada.

00:03:59.078 --> 00:04:00.030
It was beautiful.

00:04:00.030 --> 00:04:01.290
Committed to a lie?

00:04:01.290 --> 00:04:03.420
- Oh, I probably lied about
watching someone's movie

00:04:03.420 --> 00:04:05.183
that I have not seen sometime this week.

00:04:05.183 --> 00:04:06.016
It was yours.
- Was it one of mine?

00:04:06.016 --> 00:04:07.767
- All of of yours.
- It was one of mine, yeah.

00:04:07.767 --> 00:04:09.640
- Caused chaos [laughing] by accident?

00:04:09.640 --> 00:04:10.608
- [chuckling] Every day.

00:04:10.608 --> 00:04:11.441
- Every single day.

00:04:11.441 --> 00:04:12.420
- Every day.
- Right now.

00:04:12.420 --> 00:04:14.190
- Last time you felt really seen?

00:04:14.190 --> 00:04:16.860
- By our, what we did with Emily Henry,

00:04:16.860 --> 00:04:19.680
and when you said the kindest
things about me yesterday.

00:04:19.680 --> 00:04:20.513
- [Tom] Aw.
- They're always

00:04:20.513 --> 00:04:22.200
